label: Luzern, Zentral- und Hochschulbibliothek, P 6 4°

metadata.label: Place of Origin (English)
metadata.value: Paris, for the Archdiocese of Bamberg

metadata.label: Summary (English)
metadata.value: This Book of Hours belonged to the town clerk and alderman of Solothurn, Franz Haffner (1609-1671). It is set up for use in the Archdiocese of Bamberg and is written in northern Bavarian dialect, but it belongs to a group of devotional books that were produced in Paris and then exported to Nuremberg for sale.

metadata.label: Persons
metadata.value: Author: Aegidius, Romanus; Author: Bernardinus, Senensis; Author: Gregorius I, Papa; Former possessor: Haffner, Franz; Author: Johannes, von Neumarkt; Author: Marquard, von Lindau
